The defendant Eric J Gosh was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Present/Cause Fraud.Insur.Claim(<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.395(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

BY THE COURT:

BY THE COURT:
15CF355 Count 1, 16CF198 Counts 2 & 3: 
Sentence withheld. 
Placed on probation for 24 months: 
Pay restitution totaling $5,735.00 to be paid within 12 months of todays date (9/15/2017). 
$3,335.00 to be paid within 6 months of todays date. 
Balance to be paid within 6 months thereafter. 
Obtain and maintain full-time employment or schooling or a combination of both equaling full-time.
Not to have any contact, direct/indirect without agens prior permission with Mr. Scott or his residence. 
Agent shall have discretion to order Mr. Gosh to participate in any counseling or programming that the agent feels is necessary and appropriate during period of supervision. 
Court is not aware if agent can determine early discharge but Court will not reduce the period of probation.  
Pay costs and DNA surcharges on each count. 

16CF198 Count 1 - 
Court defers entry of judgment.  
This count will be dismissed if the defendant successfully completes the period of probation imposed on 15CF355 Count 1, 16CF198 Counts 2 & 3.
